title: Average folks optimistic on economy as stock market goes gangbusters
text: In trying to read the tea leaves of American sentiment, a pair of recent surveys have uncovered — wait for it — optimism. The stock market is going gangbusters in 2020, and for those invested, the record highs attained by the Dow, S&P 500 and Nasdaq have brought welcome gains.

title: Phase One U.S. China Trade Goals Are Insurmountable
text: The Phase One Trade Deal between Trump and China calls for $200 billion in additional exports from the U.S. to China over two years.

title: How A Decline In Mean Reversion May Be Hurting Value Investors
text: Value investing has done poorly in recent years. Researchers believe that a decline in mean reversion may be partially responsible for value investing's slump.

title: Pork markets to become a big winner in the US-China trade truce
text: Just a day after the United States and China signed a phase 1 trade deal, The US Department of Agriculture released a report that delivers another optimistic message to US farmers: Chinese demand for pork is likely to boost the US pork markets in 2020.

title: Happy New Year on the Stock Markets in 2020?
text: 2019 was a great year for stock markets, but what will 2020 bring? There’s a good chance that the upward trend will continue, although it might not be as strong as last year.
